The paper deals with the problem of gathering mobile agents in the plane, which is a classic problem in distributed computing (cs.DC). The agents are equipped with compasses, clocks, and a common unit of distance, which suggests that the paper may also be relevant to robotics (cs.RO) and sensor networks (cs.SI). The fact that the agents execute the same deterministic algorithm and travel at the same speed suggests that the paper may also be relevant to multi-agent systems (cs.MA) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
